1 AN ACT relating to jailer service cards issued by the Secretary of State.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 ïƒ¢SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 14 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section, "qualified jailer" means an individual who:
6 (a) Is currently serving or previously served as a duly elected or appointed jailer
7 in the Commonwealth of Kentucky; and
8 (b) Has not been:
9 1. Removed from office; or
10 2. Disqualified from holding office under the Constitution of Kentucky
11 or the Kentucky Revised Statutes.
12 (2) The Secretary of State shall issue a jailer service card to a qualified jailer who
13 applies to receive a card under this section. The jailer service card shall serve as
14 an acknowledgement by the Secretary of State that the jailer service cardholder
15 currently serves or previously served as a jailer in the Commonwealth of
16 Kentucky.
17 (3) The Secretary of State shall promulgate administrative regulations in accordance
18 with KRS Chapter 13A to establish:
19 (a) Protocols for verifying the identity of the applicant and that the applicant is
20 a qualified jailer;
21 (b) The form of applications for the issuance of a jailer service card;
22 (c) The design and printed content of the jailer service card which shall, at a
23 minimum:
24 1. Distinguish between currently serving jailers and jailers who have
25 previously served;
26 2. Identify the cardholder; and
27 3. Identify the county in which the cardholder holds or held the office of
